Uses of Class
ui.outputpanels.OutputPanel

  • Packages that use OutputPanel 
    Package Description
    ui.outputpanels
    Provides an abstraction of tabbed panels for displaying different forms of output, including the ODEWorkspace, its representation graphs and data.

    • Uses of OutputPanel in ui.outputpanels

      Subclasses of OutputPanel in ui.outputpanels 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ComponentGraphPanel
      This class extends GraphPanel, is specialized for plotting graphs with one variable on each of the axis, where the x-axis represents the independent variable t.
      class  DataPanel
      DataPanel displays the internal ODE curve point data.
      class  Graph3DPanel
      This class defines the GraphPanel that allows for a 3D plot of three variables Features not support yet: PopupListener and Popup menu, Zoom box, print, export
      class  GraphPanel
      GraphPanel is an abstract class defining one of two types of OutputPanels inside a TabbedOutputPanel for an ODEWorkspace, the other class being a DataPanel.
      class  MultiGraphPanel
      MultiGraphPanels draw plots of several variables against a single independent variable.
      class  PhaseGraphPanel
      PhaseGraphPanels are GraphPanels that represent a graph of two of an ODE's independent variables.
